In one embodiment, the present disclosure provides a method for transmitting a protection signal in a power conversion device. The method for transmitting a protection signal comprises the following steps:
Step 210: detecting one of a plurality of power semiconductor switches in the power semiconductor switch module and a driving signal transmitting circuit, and when one of the plurality of power semiconductor switches, or the driving signal transmitting circuit or the combination of both is/are malfunctioning, generating a fault signal;
Step 220: generating a corresponding fault pulse signal according to the fault signal;
Step 230: using an isolated pulse transforming unit to receive the fault pulse signal, and outputting a protection pulse signal;
Step 240: generating a protection signal according to the protection pulse signal;
Step 250: receiving the protection signal; and
Step 260: generating a control-terminal turn-off signal according to the protection signal, and transmitting the control-terminal turn-off signal to the power semiconductor switch module to turn off the power semiconductor switch module.

claim.claim-text:
A power conversion device, comprising:
a power semiconductor switch module (150), comprising a plurality of power semiconductor switches (1521∼152N);
a driving signal transmitting circuit (120) electrically coupled to the power semiconductor switch module (150), and configured to receive a control signal and generate a driving signal according to the control signal to drive the conduction or non-conduction of the power semiconductor switch module (150);
a plurality of fault detecting circuits (1401∼140N), wherein each of the plurality of fault detecting circuits (1401∼140N) is configured to correspondingly detect one of the plurality of power semiconductor switches (1521∼152N) and/or the driving signal transmitting circuit (120), and generate a fault signal when one of the plurality of power semiconductor switches (1521∼152N) and/or the driving signal transmitting circuit (120) is malfunctioning;
a protection signal transmitting circuit (130), comprising:
an isolated pulse transforming unit (134) coupled to the plurality of fault detecting circuits (1401∼140N), and configured to receive a corresponding fault pulse signal generated according to the fault signal, and to output a protection pulse signal; and
a control circuit (110) coupled to the driving signal transmitting circuit (120) and the isolated pulse transforming unit (134), and configured to generate the control signal and receive a protection signal generated according to the protection pulse signal, and generate a control-terminal turn-off signal according to the protection signal to turn off the power semiconductor switch module (150).

The power conversion device of claim 1, wherein the protection signal transmitting circuit (130) further comprises:
a protection signal processing unit (132) electrically coupled between the isolated pulse transforming unit (134) and the control circuit (110), and configured to receive the protection pulse signal, wherein the protection signal processing unit (132) generates the protection signal according to the protection pulse signal and transmits the protection signal to the control circuit (110);
wherein the protection signal processing unit (132) simultaneously transmits the protection signal to the control circuit (110) and the driving signal transmitting circuit (120);
wherein the driving signal transmitting circuit (120) is configured to generate a driving-terminal turn-off signal according to the protection signal and transmit the driving-terminal turn-off signal to turn off the power semiconductor switch module (150).

The power conversion device of claim 3, wherein the isolated pulse transforming unit (134) comprises:
a plurality of pulse transformers (1341∼134N), wherein each of the plurality of pulse transformers (1341∼134N) comprises an input winding (Input1), a magnetic core and an output winding (Output1); the input winding (Input1) of each of the plurality of pulse transformers (1341∼134N) is correspondingly electrically coupled to the one of the plurality of protection signal generating units (1361-1361 N); and the plurality of output windings (Output1∼OutputN) of the plurality of pulse transformers (1341∼134N) are serially connected in turn, and are electrically coupled to the protection signal processing unit (132);
or the isolated pulse transforming unit (134) comprises:
a pulse transformer, comprising a plurality of input windings, (Input1∼InputN) a magnetic core and an output winding (Output), wherein each of the plurality of input windings (Input1∼InputN) is correspondingly electrically coupled to the one of the plurality of protection signal generating units (1361∼136N), and the output winding (Output 1) is electrically coupled to the protection signal processing unit (132);
or the isolated pulse transforming unit (134) comprises:
a plurality of pulse transformers, wherein one of the plurality of pulse transformers comprises an input winding (Input 1), a magnetic core and an output winding (Output 1); another one of the plurality of pulse transformers comprises a plurality of input windings (Input (N-n+1)∼Input N), a magnetic core and an output winding (Output N); each of the plurality of input windings (Input 1∼Input N) is correspondingly electrically coupled to the one of the plurality of protection signal generating units (1361∼136N); and the plurality of output windings (Output 1∼Output N) are serially connected in turn, and are electrically coupled to the protection signal processing unit (132).

The power conversion device of claim 1, wherein the driving signal transmitting circuit (120) comprises:
a driving primary-side unit (122) configured to receive the control signal and generate a driving pulse signal according to the control signal;
a signal magnetic-isolating unit (124) configured to receive and transmit the driving pulse signal; and
a driving secondary-side unit (126) configured to receive the driving pulse signal and convert the driving pulse signal into the driving signal to drive the power semiconductor switch module (150);
or the driving signal transmitting circuit (120) comprises:
a driving primary-side unit (122) configured to receive the control signal and generate a primary-side signal according to the control signal;
a signal light-isolating unit (124) configured to receive and transmit the primary-side signal; and
a driving secondary-side unit (126) configured to receive the primary-side signal and convert the primary-side signal into the driving signal to drive the power semiconductor switch module (150).

The power conversion device of claim 6, wherein the signal magnetic-isolating unit (124) comprises:
a plurality of driving pulse-isolation transformers (1241∼124N), wherein each of the plurality of driving pulse-isolation transformers (1241∼124N) comprises an input winding (Input 1), a magnetic core and an output winding (Output 1); the output winding (Output 1) of each of the plurality of driving pulse-isolation transformers (1241∼124N) is correspondingly electrically coupled to the one of the plurality of driving secondary-side units (1261∼126N); and the plurality of input windings (Input1∼Input N) of the plurality of driving pulse-isolation transformers (1241∼124N) are serially connected in turn, and electrically coupled to the driving primary-side unit (122);
or wherein the signal magnetic-isolating unit (124) comprises:
a driving pulse-isolation transformer (1241), comprising an input winding (Input 1), a magnetic core and a plurality of output windings (Output 1-Output N), wherein each of the plurality of output windings (Output 1-Output N) is correspondingly electrically coupled to the one of the plurality of driving secondary-side units (1261∼126N), and the input winding (Input 1) is electrically coupled to the driving primary-side unit (122);
or wherein the signal magnetic-isolating unit (124) comprises:
a plurality of driving pulse-isolation transformers (1241∼124N), wherein one of the plurality of driving pulse-isolation transformers (1241∼124N) comprises an input winding (Input 1), a magnetic core and an output winding (Output 1); another one of the plurality of driving pulse-isolation transformers (1241∼124N) comprises an input winding (Input N), a magnetic core and a plurality of output winding (Output (N-n+1)∼Output N); each of the plurality of output windings (Output 1-Output N) is correspondingly electrically coupled to the one of the plurality of driving secondary-side units (1261∼126N); and the plurality of input windings (Input 1∼Input N) are serially connected in turn and electrically coupled to the driving primary-side unit (122).

A method for transmitting a protection signal of a power conversion device, comprising:
detecting a plurality of power semiconductor switches (1521∼152N) within a power semiconductor switch module (150) and/or a driving signal transmitting circuit, and generating a fault signal when one of the plurality of power semiconductor switches (1521∼152N) and/or a driving signal transmitting circuit (120) is malfunctioning;
using an isolated pulse transforming unit (134) to receive a corresponding fault pulse signal generated according to the fault signal, and to output a protection pulse signal;
receiving a protection signal generated according to the protection pulse signal; and
generating a control-terminal turn-off signal according to the protection signal, and transmitting the control-terminal turn-off signal to turn off the power semiconductor switch module (150).
